About.

Xuedan ZOU is currently a master student majoring in Computer Science with a concentration in Digital Arts at Dartmouth College. He has earned his B.E. in Hunan University, majoring in both Computer Science and Industrial Design. He is now serving as the Research Assistant at Empower Research Lab at Dartmouth College. His current research interest mainly lies in Human-Computer Interaction.


Personally, he is interested in most video games (real gamer since he was about 3), mangas, graphic novels and great music (like city pop)! He believes he is one of the few people who is particularly interested in the city Tokyoï¼Œwhere he states can evoke a strong personal emotion and inspire his creativity. He enjoys watching random urban walking videos in 1990s Tokyo and mid 80s ~ early 00s Japanese CMs. He has spent over 1000 hour in a city-building game named Cities Skylines. The rightside video of this page shows how his city in the game merges with the reality.
